fields.Title: File Cabinet: "There it still is -- inviting you t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There it still is -- inviting you to...

fields.Title: You: ""Yes.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes."

fields.Title: Volition: "Whatever's hidden here is hidden we..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Whatever's hidden here is hidden well. Concentration isn't enough, only a trained accountant, with a background in logistics, would be able to *really* make sense of it. However there *is* a little hand-written note, stuck on the side of the drawer.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Good." He turns away from the file..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good." He turns away from the file cabinet. "This is probably not relevant to our case anyway. After all, we are not investigating an accounting mystery."

fields.Title: You: "Close the drawer. [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: Close the drawer. [Leave.]

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "It's hard to make sense of this thi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's hard to make sense of this thicket of company names, dates, quantities, and percentages. You try to focus, but the lines are getting blurry...

fields.Title: You: "Leave the folders alone for now."
fields.Dialogue Text: Leave the folders alone for now.

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "It appears to be a to-do list writt..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It appears to be a to-do list written in large, uneven capital letters:

fields.Title: You: "Open the drawer."
fields.Dialogue Text: Open the drawer.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "It's probably on rails."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's probably on rails.

fields.Title: You: "Browse through the folders."
fields.Dialogue Text: Browse through the folders.

fields.Title: Volition: "You're trying hard, but the data he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're trying hard, but the data here is *unbelievably* dry. Something about containers...

fields.Title: You: "Read the note."
fields.Dialogue Text: Read the note.
fields.Alternate1: Take another look at the note.

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "REMEMBER, LEO! * EVRART'S SHOES..."
fields.Dialogue Text:
REMEMBER, LEO!

* EVRART'S SHOES
* SPECIAL WHIRLING BORSCHT
* WATER EVRART'S PLANTS
* SWEEP OFFICE FLOOR
* MORE BANNERS

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "...and the same materials being han..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...and the same materials being handed over to companies inside Revachol. Couron, Coal City, La Delta, and Jamrock are listed among the many districts where the imports are being sold.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "What is so special about this *bors..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What is so special about this *borscht*? Code for drugs? Booze? Blood?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The leader of the Débardeurs' Unio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The leader of the Débardeurs' Union, Evrart Claire, has someone running errands for him." He points to the list. "Nothing incriminating here, though."
fields.Alternate1: "Evrart has someone running errands for him." He points to the list. "Nothing incriminating here, though."
fields.Alternate2: "The Débardeurs' Union leader, Evrart Claire, has Leo running errands for him." He points to the list. "Nothing incriminating here, though."
fields.Alternate3: "Evrart has Leo running errands for him." He points to the list. "Nothing incriminating here, though."

fields.Title: You: ""If I let my eyes go completely out..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If I let my eyes go completely out of focus, all shapes start melting into each other."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Right." The lieutenant's expressio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right." The lieutenant's expression stiffens. "This is probably not relevant to our case. After all, we are not investigating an accounting mystery."

fields.Title: Logic: "The *special* borscht seems a bit o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The *special* borscht seems a bit odd in the list.

fields.Title: You: "Anything interesting? (Browse them...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Anything interesting? (Browse them.)

fields.Title: You: ""No, of course not.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, of course not."

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "The drawer slides shut smoothly."
fields.Dialogue Text: The drawer slides shut smoothly.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Evrart Claire, probably -- the hea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Evrart Claire, probably -- the head of the Débardeurs' Union." He inspects the note. "One of his aides must have left it. Nothing incriminating here."
fields.Alternate1: He inspects the note. "One of his aides must have left it. Nothing incriminating here."
fields.Alternate2: "Evrart Claire, probably -- the head of the Débardeurs' Union." He inspects the note. "Leo must have left it. Nothing incriminating here."
fields.Alternate3: He inspects the note. "Leo must have left it. Nothing incriminating here."

fields.Title: Volition: "You are a police officer, not a spi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You are a police officer, not a spiritual healer. You can focus the normal way by turning your attention to something and not letting go.

fields.Title: You: ""Never mind the note." (Close the d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Never mind the note." (Close the drawer.)

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "On second glance, someone has forgo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: On second glance, someone has forgotten to properly close one of the drawers.

fields.Title: You: "Look at the note."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look at the note.

fields.Title: Volition: "Look how blurry all the lines on th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look how blurry all the lines on these papers are -- how unwieldy your own willpower is to yourself. You're like an absurdist Samaran monk -- focusing through not focusing.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Is that what you're doing with tho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is that what you're doing with those folders over there?"

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "All items on the list have been cro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: All items on the list have been crossed out and the note itself is crumpled.

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "REMEMBER, LEO! * EVRART'S SHOES..."
fields.Dialogue Text:
REMEMBER, LEO!

* EVRART'S SHOES
* SPECIAL WHIRLING BORSCHT
* WATER EVRART'S PLANTS
* SWEEP OFFICE FLOOR
* MORE BANNERS

fields.Title: You: "(Turn to the lieutenant.) "Look, Ki..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Turn to the lieutenant.) "Look, Kim, a to-do note with a list of errands for *Evrart*."

fields.Title: You: "Ignore drawer for now. [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: Ignore drawer for now. [Leave.]

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "The file cabinet stands steady as e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The file cabinet stands steady as ever and the unlocked drawer slides out to greet you.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "...let's see what's inside, he thin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...let's see what's inside, he thinks.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Hermeneutics was almost within your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hermeneutics was almost within your grasp, but now only vague letters float before your eyes. Less meaningful, but aesthetically more pleasing.

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "All items on the list have been cro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: All items on the list have been crossed out and the note itself is crumpled.

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "The drawer slides shut smoothly."
fields.Dialogue Text: The drawer slides shut smoothly.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's *unfortunate* for the Union t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's *unfortunate* for the Union to just leave their paperwork lying around like this..."

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "Hundreds of documents containing lo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hundreds of documents containing logistical data. Two kinds of transactions stand out: materials coming into Revachol from the outside world -- from Mundi, Graad, and even Iilmaraa...

fields.Title: You: "Force yourself to go through the fo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Force yourself to go through the folders.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""My thought exactly, officer." He t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "My thought exactly, officer." He turns away from the file cabinet. "Shall we?"

fields.Title: You: "Ignore the note."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ignore the note.

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "The drawer opens smoothly. Inside i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The drawer opens smoothly. Inside is a well-organized selection of brown folders.

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "You already went through all of the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You already went through all of these.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Doesn't look too incriminating -- b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Doesn't look too incriminating -- but still feels like a *find*.

fields.Title: You: ""Let's just get back to work, lieut..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's just get back to work, lieutenant."

fields.Title: File Cabinet: "The file cabinet stands steady as e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The file cabinet stands steady as ever. Sliding out a drawer presents you the folders you already went through. On top of them is the handwritten note.

fields.Title: You: "Could I actually focus through *not..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Could I actually focus through *not* focusing?
